title: Leaked Audition Tape Hints at MAJOR Star Wars Villain Appearance for Episode IX
body:
Leaked Audition Tape Hints at MAJOR Star Wars Villain Appearance for Episode IX

A leaked audition tape from actor Adam Templar has pushed the theory that one of the biggest Star Wars villains in Grand Admiral Thrawn may appear in the final chapter of the new trilogy.

Templar begins the audition by introducing himself and then telling the audience that it is his audition tape for Grand Admiral Thrawn. What’s interesting about the tape is that he actually applied blue skin…

It's ya girl Chaos, your friendly neighborhood dragon girl bringing my own brand of oddness to Tumblr since December 2013.
26 y/o, cis female, part-time RPer, pansexual, unabashed self-shipper deeply in love with my F/O's Piccolo, Perfect Cell, and Frieza as well as pals with my platonic F/O's Ginyu and Whis, American, chaotic good, INFJ-T personality, engaged to my wonderful dork @sparkinclark, professional moron, proud Fur Mama, honorary Ginyu Force member, Pokemon trainer (Dragon Tamer class), Mother of Dragon-Types with 3 shiny Salamences to my name, Gryffindor, Asperger's, Rowlet sanctuary owner, interracial dating supporter, owl lover, morbid to the core, and with all the humor and intrigue of a baked potato. TERFs, radfems, homophobes, and racists need not interact.
Current fandoms: Pokemon, Dragon Ball, Bojack Horseman, Overwatch, Aggretsuko, Gravity Falls, Super Mario Bros, TF2, Legend of Zelda, The Walking Dead, Hellsing.
Follow me on Twitter @ChaosDragoness for shitposts and reblogs of owls.

summary: In Review: Solo: A Star Wars’ Story reviewed. A long Time Ago, This Week
title: In Review: Solo: A Star Wars’ Story reviewed. A long Time Ago, This Week
body:
In Review: Solo: A Star Wars’ Story reviewed. A long Time Ago, This Week

I never felt the need to watch a film that told me Han Solo’s back story because the character was such a cliché that I felt that I already knew it. For me, Star Wars didn’t exactly have depth. As an example of what scholar Fredrick Jameson called “the nostalgia mode”, the original movie relied on audiences’ collective memory of other movies to provide its characters with more than one dimension.

title: SOLO: A STAR WARS STORY Exclusive Interview with Woody Harrelson #HanSoloEvent
body:
SOLO: A STAR WARS STORY Exclusive Interview with Woody Harrelson #HanSoloEvent

As his film career is filled with comedies, I expected Woody Harrelson to be funny – and, indeed his is.  He’s also charismatic, kind, vibrant and the kind of guy you’d love to travel with or hang out with on the weekend because you just know you’d have a great time.  Thanks to my partnership with Disney, I had the chance to attend an exclusive interview with Woody Harrelson right after the world…
